SIMPLE: unlace
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unlace
<hw>Un*lace"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>lace</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To loose by undoing a lacing; <as>as, to
<ex>unlace</ex> a shoe</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To loose the dress of; to undress; hence, to expose;
to disgrace.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What's the matter,⟦br⟧
That you <qex>unlace</qex> your reputation thus?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>To loose, and take off, as a
bonnet from a sail, or to cast off, as any lacing in any part of the
rigging of a vessel.</def> <rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unlade</ent>⟦br⟧
